<Layout title="CPAs &amp; Accountants · Florida CPA Partner Hub — Tax Planning, 1031 Exchanges, SALT Cap &amp; Form 1084 Self-Employed Mortgage Coordination Specialist" description="Florida CPA / Accountant partner hub educating buyers, sellers, and self-employed borrowers on what licensed Certified Public Accountants do in real estate transactions: mortgage interest deduction strategy under IRC Section 163(h) with $750K acquisition debt cap post-TCJA; SALT cap navigation under IRC Section 164(b)(6) with $10K combined state and local tax cap; Section 121 primary home gain exclusion at $250K single / $500K joint with 2-of-5-year ownership and use requirement; 1031 like-kind exchange coordination under IRC Section 1031 with 45-day identification and 180-day completion timelines plus qualified intermediary coordination; depreciation strategy under IRC Section 168 at 27.5-year residential and 39-year commercial recovery periods; cost segregation studies for accelerated depreciation; passive activity loss limitations under IRC Section 469 for investment property; Section 199A QBI deduction for pass-through real estate businesses; basis tracking through ownership and capital improvement periods; FIRPTA Foreign Investment in Real Property Tax Act compliance for foreign-seller transactions. For self-employed mortgage borrowers, CPA-prepared Form 1084 cash-flow addback documentation recovering entity-level depreciation, amortization, and other non-cash deductions making qualifying income properly visible to mortgage lender under Fannie Mae B3-3.4-02 partnership and S-corp analysis and B3-3.3-02 Schedule C self-employed income analysis. CPA credentials: licensed CPA through state Board of Accountancy with 150 semester hours education and Uniform CPA Exam; PFS Personal Financial Specialist credential through AICPA; MST Master of Science in Taxation or LLM in Tax for advanced tax specialization; EA Enrolled Agent IRS-licensed tax practitioner; ABV Accredited in Business Valuation; CGMA Chartered Global Management Accountant; AICPA Tax Section and FICPA Florida Institute of CPAs membership. Top CPA firms: Big 4 Deloitte EY KPMG PwC plus national BDO Grant Thornton RSM plus Florida regional Berkowitz Pollack Brant MBAF Crowe Daszkal Bolton. Florida wealth migration from California New York Illinois New Jersey driven by no-state-income-tax advantage with multi-state tax filings during migration year. Florida no-state-income-tax interaction with $10K SALT cap providing full cap availability for property tax deduction. Partner-as-borrower CTA at bottom routing CPAs looking for mortgages on their own home to dedicated CPA-as-borrower mortgage guide with S-corp partnership principal W-2 + K-1 documentation under Fannie Mae B3-3.4-02." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/cpas-accountants/">
